r and President of the Brain Trauma Foundation in New York City and Palo Alto.\r\n\r\nHe completed the MD/PhD program at Cornell University Medical College. During his residency training in neurosurgery at New York Presbyterian Hospital, he invented and patented several neurosurgical devices that are currently used worldwide. After residency, he joined the faculty at New York Presbyterian Hospital-Cornell Medical Center and was a founder of the Brain Trauma Foundation (BTF) in 1986. The mission of the BTF is to improve the outcome of patients with traumatic brain injury (TBI). He joined the neurosurgery faculty at Stanford in February 2014.'),(943,13,'_team_member_detail_0_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(944,13,'team_member_detail_1_add_image',''),(945,13,'_team_member_detail_1_add_image','field_56a098c6429f4'),(946,13,'team_member_detail_1_add_name','Ernest Santin'),(947,13,'_team_member_detail_1_add_name','field_56a098f2429f5'),(948,13,'team_member_detail_1_add_job_title','CEO'),(949,13,'_team_member_detail_1_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(950,13,'team_member_detail_1_add_content','Mr. Santin has 35 years experience in building and managing emerging growth companies. He has founded two successful venture backed technology companies. The first, Strato Medical Corp, a medical device company was acquired by Pfizer in 1990. The second, Sensitech Inc, a cold chain visibility solution provider was acquired by United Technologies in 2006. During his career Ernie has raised over $50 million in venture capital and invented products in the medical and food industries.'),(951,13,'_team_member_detail_1_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(952,13,'team_member_detail_2_add_image',''),(953,13,'_team_member_detail_2_add_image','field_56a098c6429f4'),(954,13,'team_member_detail_2_add_name','Daniel Beeler'),(955,13,'_team_member_detail_2_add_name','field_56a098f2429f5'),(956,13,'team_member_detail_2_add_job_title','CTO'),(957,13,'_team_member_detail_2_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(958,13,'team_member_detail_2_add_content','Mr. Beeler joined SyncThink in 2010 and serves as CTO. Dan has been lead engineer for several companies in the Boston area and has designed technology products in large-scale data acquisition, eCommerce, and medicine. Dan holds a degree in Physics from Pomona College. He has also contributed research towards planetary science, adaptive optics, and galaxy formation at Caltech and Observatories of the Carnegie Institute of Washington. His expertise in image analysis serves as a key asset for SyncThink.'),(959,13,'_team_member_detail_2_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(960,13,'team_member_detail_3_add_image','307'),(961,13,'_team_member_detail_3_add_image','field_56a098c6429f4'),(962,13,'team_member_detail_3_add_name','Alan Quasha'),(963,13,'_team_member_detail_3_add_name','field_56a098f2429f5'),(964,13,'team_member_detail_3_add_job_title','Board Member'),(965,13,'_team_member_detail_3_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(966,13,'team_member_detail_3_add_content','Mr. Alan Quasha is the President of Quadrant Management, Inc., a principal investment management firm. Quadrant and its affiliates manage over $3 billion.  He is also the Co-Chairman of Carret Asset Management, LLC and Chairman of Brean Capital. Over the last 20 years, Mr. Quasha has successfully invested in over 80 companies in the United States as well as in emerging markets. Many of these investments were restructuring and turnaround situations involving significant hands-on operating experience. He has served as a director of Richemont SA from 1988 up until the time he joined the Board of Compagnie Financire Richemont SA (a world leading luxury goods company) and was Chief Executive Officer of North American Resources Limited, formerly a joint venture between Richemont and the Quasha family between 1988 and 1998. He is also Chairman of HKN, Inc. (a publicly traded independent oil and gas company) and Chairman of the American Brain Trauma Foundation. He was the former Governor of the American Stock Exchange, a past director of American Express Funds, and former Chairman of the Visiting Committee of Harvard Universitys Weatherhead Center for International Affairs. Mr. Quasha holds a Bachelor\'s degree from Harvard College, a MBA from Harvard Business School, a Master of Law degree from New York University Law School, and a Doctorate of Law from the Harvard Law School.'),(967,13,'_team_member_detail_3_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(968,13,'team_member_detail_4_add_image','179'),(969,13,'_team_member_detail_4_add_image','field_56a098c6429f4'),(970,13,'team_member_detail_4_add_name','John van Merkensteijn III'),(971,13,'_team_member_detail_4_add_name','field_56a098f2429f5'),(972,13,'team_member_detail_4_add_job_title','Board Member'),(973,13,'_team_member_detail_4_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(974,13,'team_member_detail_4_add_content','Mr. van Merkensteijn has been an investment banker and attorney for over 45 years. As an attorney, he was a founder and partner of Evans & van Merkensteijn and was of Counsel to, and a partner of, Coudert Brothers, (New York) and a founding partner of Gottesman, Evans & van Merkensteijn, (London). As an investment banker and a principal, Mr. van Merkensteijn has been involved in numerous acquisitions and dispositions of companies with a variety of assets. He was a founder and Director of I-Behavior, Inc., a direct marketing database firm which was sold for $400 million. Mr. van Merkensteijn graduated from Yale University in 1965 with a B.A. and the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1968 with an LLB.'),(975,13,'_team_member_detail_4_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(976,13,'team_member_detail_5_add_image',''),(977,13,'_team_member_detail_5_add_image','field_56a098c6429f4'),(978,13,'team_member_detail_5_add_name','Kevin Quinn'),(979,13,'_team_member_detail_5_add_name','field_56a098f2429f5'),(980,13,'team_member_detail_5_add_job_title','Board Member'),(981,13,'_team_member_detail_5_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(982,13,'team_member_detail_5_add_content','Kevin is currently the founder of Genki Advisory, an advisory and investment firm. For over 20 years, Kevin was employed at Goldman, Sachs & Co. where he worked with high tech companies in the firms investment banking division. Kevin served in a number of senior roles in Goldman Sachs New York, San Francisco and Tokyo offices. He retired as a partner from Goldman Sachs in 2012. Today, Kevin is an active angel investor and an adjunct professor at Columbia Business Schools Lang Center for Entrepreneurship. He is a graduate of Columbia College and Columbia Business School.'),(983,13,'_team_member_detail_5_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(984,13,'team_member_detail','7'),(985,13,'_team_member_detail','field_56a09834429f3'),(986,140,'add_title','Behind every great product is a <strong>great team. '),(987,140,'_add_title','field_56a092fb429e9'),(988,140,'add_content','Preserve and cherish that pale blue dot. Flatland, corpus callosum, Hypatia, Apollonius of Perga the sky calls to us? Dream of the mind\'s eye something incredible is waiting to be known, venture a billion trillion culture light years science Sea of Tranquility prime number, vastness is bearable only through love? '),(989,140,'_add_content','field_56a0997a5fddd'),(990,140,'add_banner',''),(991,140,'_add_banner','field_56a0930d429ea'),(992,140,'add_banner_title','The team at headquarers in Boston, MA'),(993,140,'_add_banner_title','field_56a0937b429eb'),(994,140,'add_sub_title','Changing head trauma diagnosis from coast to coast.'),(995,140,'_add_sub_title','field_56a093cb429ec'),(996,140,'add_sub_content','Preserve and cherish that pale blue dot. Flatland, corpus callosum, Hypatia, Apollonius of Perga the sky calls to us? Dream of the mind\'s eye something incredible is waiting to be known, venture a billion trillion culture light years science Sea of Tranquility prime number, vastness is b