er'),(4249,414,'_team_member_detail_4_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(4250,414,'team_member_detail_4_add_content','Mr. van Merkensteijn has been an investment banker and attorney for over 45 years. As an attorney, he was a founder and partner of Evans & van Merkensteijn and was of Counsel to, and a partner of, Coudert Brothers, (New York) and a founding partner of Gottesman, Evans & van Merkensteijn, (London). As an investment banker and a principal, Mr. van Merkensteijn has been involved in numerous acquisitions and dispositions of companies with a variety of assets. He was a founder and Director of I-Behavior, Inc., a direct marketing database firm which was sold for $400 million. Mr. van Merkensteijn graduated from Yale University in 1965 with a B.A. and the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1968 with an LLB.'),(4251,414,'_team_member_detail_4_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(4252,414,'team_member_detail_5_add_image',''),(4253,414,'_team_member_detail_5_add_image','field_56a098c6429f4'),(4254,414,'team_member_detail_5_add_name','Kevin Quinn'),(4255,414,'_team_member_detail_5_add_name','field_56a098f2429f5'),(4256,414,'team_member_detail_5_add_job_title','Board Member'),(4257,414,'_team_member_detail_5_add_job_title','field_56a09913429f6'),(4258,414,'team_member_detail_5_add_content','Kevin is currently the founder of Genki Advisory, an advisory and investment firm. For over 20 years, Kevin was employed at Goldman, Sachs & Co. where he worked with high tech companies in the firms investment banking division. Kevin served in a number of senior roles in Goldman Sachs New York, San Francisco and Tokyo offices. He retired as a partner from Goldman Sachs in 2012. Today, Kevin is an active angel investor and an adjunct professor at Columbia Business Schools Lang Center for Entrepreneurship. He is a graduate of Columbia College and Columbia Business School.'),(4259,414,'_team_member_detail_5_add_content','field_56a09933429f7'),(4260,414,'team_member_det